{"submission_id":"sub_2be859a7ffd3f88c","run_id":"2026-06-20T12-37-53-808Z_1885472-521ad4e5_ingest_meeting-doc-124126","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T13:40:24.705Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:2be859a7ffd3f88c6d4795537d26cadda273d99d6c365ca389a7a9120bca83d2","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124126","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_recovery_ratio_long_term","label":"Farebox recovery ratio definition","raw_text":"(1) Farebox recovery ratio has a long-term focus. It includes costs that are not funded in the current year, except in an accounting-ledger sense, but are, in effect, passed on to future years. Those costs include depreciation and interest on long-term debt. Approximately 20% (and sometimes more) of MTA costs are not recovered in the current year from farebox revenues, other operating revenues or subsidies.","payload":{"claim_text":"Farebox recovery ratio has a long-term focus. It includes costs that are not funded in the current year...including depreciation and interest on long-term debt. Approximately 20% (and sometimes more) of MTA costs are not recovered in the current year from farebox revenues, other operating revenues or subsidies.","subject":"Farebox recovery ratio","description":"Definition of the farebox recovery ratio methodology as used in this document"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124126","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_124126#p001_c0004","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_124126/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_c0004","text_sha256":"sha256:73cc3d200531fbd139d6976bf921378f957b33ed548edbf51130734badbb39cc","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_20d6ad805c084c0e","run_id":"2026-06-20T12-37-53-808Z_1885472-521ad4e5_ingest_meeting-doc-124126","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T13:40:48.627Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:20d6ad805c084c0e459a339396e087b665b44a4507e1ef50b04a6433b4663c03","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124126","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_operating_ratio_definition","label":"Farebox operating ratio definition","raw_text":"(2) Farebox operating ratio focuses on Agency operating financial performance. It reflects the way MTA meets its statutory and bond-covenant budget-balancing requirements, and it excludes certain costs that are not subject to Agency control, but are provided centrally by the MTA.","payload":{"claim_text":"Farebox operating ratio focuses on Agency operating financial performance. It reflects the way MTA meets its statutory and bond-covenant budget-balancing requirements, and it excludes certain costs that are not subject to Agency control, but are provided centrally by the MTA.","subject":"Farebox operating ratio","description":"Definition of the farebox operating ratio methodology as used in this document"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124126","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_124126#p001_c0005","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_124126/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_c0005","text_sha256":"sha256:89734ba2fdc31a9553979d727aedacebf692e562df28966a8adbffa5f650c0b3","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_c18f704a6e504130","run_id":"2026-06-20T12-37-53-808Z_1885472-521ad4e5_ingest_meeting-doc-124126","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T13:41:12.190Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:c18f704a6e504130e843db9fecd080f071475d86aaff64c1fbabfe534c48a6f4","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124126","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_methodology_note_lirr_mnr","label":"LIRR/MNR farebox calculations use revised methodology","raw_text":"(3) In the agenda materials for the Meeting of the Metro-North and Long Island Rail Road Committees, the calculations of the farebox operating and recovery ratios for the LIRR and MNR use a revised methodology to put the railroads on a more comparable basis. Those statistics, which are included in the respective financial and ridership reports of both Agencies, differ from the statistics presented in this table.","payload":{"claim_text":"In the agenda materials for the Meeting of the Metro-North and Long Island Rail Road Committees, the calculations of the farebox operating and recovery ratios for the LIRR and MNR use a revised methodology to put the railroads on a more comparable basis. Those statistics...differ from the statistics presented in this table.","subject":"LIRR/MNR farebox calculations","description":"LIRR and MNR farebox ratios in committee materials use a revised methodology that differs from this table"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_124126","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_124126#p001_c0006","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_124126/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_c0006","text_sha256":"sha256:57fa990888e327ce417992ed45661d7b339b15ef9026299a40987023ef7ee4a5","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
